section.section:
Before a licensed real estate broker may provide real estate brokerage services through a corporation, limited liability company, or partnership, the broker shall submit to the Commission a notice that states the broker's intent to provide services through a corporation or partnership. The notice shall include:
the name of the real estate broker submitting the notice;
a statement that the named individual has been designated as the broker of the firm;
the address of the firm's principal place of business and of each proposed branch office;
any trade or fictitious name that the firm intends to use while conducting the business of the firm;
a list of all the licensed associate real estate brokers and licensed real estate salespersons who will be affiliated with the broker of the firm; and
any other information that the Commission may require by regulation.
